name: Água de Cheiro
description:
The Rosario Festival takes place annually in Curitiba, Brazil and consists of valuing the people, Afro-Brazilian religions, and black culture.

The main attraction of the festival is the washing of the stairs of the Nossa Senhora do Rosario dos Homens Negros Church.
 
Scented water, plants and flowers are used in this ritual of thanksgiving and prosperity.
 
The scented water has a very characteristic aroma of roses and other aromatic plants such as basil, rosemary, lavender and rue.
